==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|lepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hleapan|hlēapan}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hlaupanan}} (cf. Dutch {{term|lopen|lang=nl}} ‘to stroll, go for a walk’, German {{term|laufen|lang=de}} ‘to run’, Danish {{term|løbe}}), from {{proto|Indo-European}} (cf. Lithuanian {{term|šlùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to become lame’, {{term|klùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to stumble’).

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|lēp}}, {{IPA|/liːp/}}, {{SAMPA|/li:p/}}
* {{audio|en-us-leap.ogg|Audio (US)}}

* {{rhymes|iːp}}

===Initialism===
'''LEAP'''

